00:17:26.430 --> 00:17:31.120
So it turns out at slow speeds,
low Reynolds number,

00:17:31.120 --> 00:17:32.200
this is true.

00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:34.480
Turns out at high Reynolds
number, this is true.

00:17:34.480 --> 00:17:37.420
And this is the simplest
experiment to show that.

00:17:37.420 --> 00:17:40.090
So what this shows is that drag
is proportional to area.

00:17:40.090 --> 00:17:45.570
So that with the same velocity,
the extra weight is

00:17:45.570 --> 00:17:51.020
balanced by the extra drag
force by exactly 4 to 1.

00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:53.010
And what that shows, now--

00:17:53.010 --> 00:17:54.850
