may be more familiar with

00:18:37.110 --> 00:18:40.230
divided by rho, the density.

00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:43.590
So we have to put some of these
guys in, some of these

00:18:43.590 --> 00:18:46.340
guys in, and some of these guys
in, and make the units

00:18:46.340 --> 00:18:48.310
come out as a force.

00:18:48.310 --> 00:18:52.090
Well, one of them we
can do right away.

00:18:52.090 --> 00:18:56.780
There's how many powers of
mass over on this side?

00:18:56.780 --> 00:18:58.290
In a force-- just one.

00:18:58.290 --> 00:18:59.380
And there's none here, yet.

00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:02.650
So we need to get one power
of mass on this side.

00:19:02.650 --> 00:19:04.350
Now, among all these
guys, which of them

00:19:04.350 --> 00:19:05.560
have mass in them?

00:19:05.560 --> 00:19:07.390
Not this one, because
you divided out.

00:19:07.390 --> 00:19:08.990
Not velocity.

00:19:08.990 --> 00:19:11.500
Only density, and density
has one power of mass.

00:19:11.500 --> 00:19:12.760
So you have to put
one density.

00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:16.330
Question.

00:19:16.330 --> 00:19:18.830
