01:00:27.650 --> 01:00:29.860
Well, if you're going to apply
all these principles, you'll

01:00:29.860 --> 01:00:32.660
find yourself wanting to change
a lot about how the

01:00:32.660 --> 01:00:35.230
course is done or how it
was done previously.

01:00:35.230 --> 01:00:36.820
Well, what are the
barriers to that?

01:00:36.820 --> 01:00:39.280
In particular, what are the
political barriers to

01:00:39.280 --> 01:00:40.530
educational change?

01:00:54.720 --> 01:00:58.810
So that by being aware of the
barriers, you're more able to

01:00:58.810 --> 01:01:03.770
go around them, surmount them,
take account of them, plan for

01:01:03.770 --> 01:01:05.380
doing it bit by bit by bit.

01:01:05.380 --> 01:01:07.960
But eventually, hopefully
designing courses in ways that

01:01:07.960 --> 01:01:10.080
you think are good for
